{
  "stem": "22972.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "At the Evian Conference, at the end, 32 countries decided not one single country could take one single Jew.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We weren't wanted anywhere in the world.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I mean, it would take me an hour of this tape-- another hour of the tape-- to go through what it took to get into what country.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The entire world was closed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But since we're in America, I'd just like to mention that America took in 19,000 Jews a year.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Now, from 1933 to 1939, when the war started, and then the borders were closed, and then the Jews were taken into concentration camps wholesale, no longer one at a time.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "In those six years, America took in six times 19,000-- 120,000 Jews came in.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "There were maybe 1,000 that came in under special circumstances.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They took in [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] people who were famous.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Famous artists, famous politicians, famous scientists.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "The rich and the-- the rich went to Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "The famous-- the famous people and the people who could really do some good for America.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Other than that, 19,000.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Shameless for America to have only taken in-- at the time, you had to have an affidavit, and I have our affidavit, which I'd like to bring into the record.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "An affidavit had to be posted by a blood relative in America.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "You had to have a rich uncle in America, which I was fortunate enough to have.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "He had to post a bond of $5,000 which, in the depression in America was quite difficult.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "You could post it-- you didn't have to post it in cash.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "You could post it in war bonds, in-- in government bonds, you could post it in the form of a mortgage on your house, which is what most people did to get their relatives in.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
